```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    FLUTTER APP (Android)                 │
│                                                         │
│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌────────┐  │
│  │  Auth    │  │ Booking  │  │ Reports  │  │Calendar│  │
│  │ Screen   │  │  CRUD    │  │Dashboard │  │  View  │  │
│  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘  └───┬────┘  │
│       │              │              │             │      │
│       └──────────────┴──────────────┴─────────────┘     │
│                            │                            │
│                    HTTP POST (JSON)                      │
│                  { action, token, data }                 │
└────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┘
                             │
                             ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              GOOGLE APPS SCRIPT (Web App)               │
│                                                         │
│  • Verify Google ID token (tokeninfo endpoint)          │
│  • Route action to handler function                     │
│  • LockService wraps all writes                         │
│  • Returns { success, data, error, timestamp }          │
│                                                         │
└──────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬────────────────────┘
       │              │              │
       ▼              ▼              ▼
┌──────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐
│  Google  │  │   Google     │  │   Google     │
│  Sheets  │  │  Calendar    │  │    Drive     │
│  (DB)    │  │  (Events)    │  │ (KTP Files)  │
└──────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘
```

### Request Lifecycle
1. Flutter collects Google `idToken` via `google_sign_in`
2. Every API call sends `POST { action, token, data }` to Apps Script Web App URL
3. Apps Script verifies token → routes to handler → acquires LockService → reads/writes Sheets
4. Response `{ success: true, data: {...} }` returned as JSON
5. Flutter updates local state and UI

### Key Architecture Decisions
| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| Auth | Stateless token verification per request — no sessions in Apps Script |
| OCR | On-device ML Kit — free, offline, no additional API keys |
| PDF | Client-side Flutter `pdf` package — no server rendering cost |
| Calendar | Server-side `CalendarApp` in Apps Script — simpler OAuth scope management |
| File storage | Google Drive via Apps Script `DriveApp` — KTP images stored as Drive files |
| Locking | `LockService.getScriptLock()` on every write — prevents race conditions |

