## 8. RISKS & LIMITATIONS

### Technical Risks
| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| Google Sheets rate limit (100 req/100s/user) | Medium | Client-side caching, batch reads, avoid polling |
| Apps Script cold start (~2–5s first request) | Low | Show loading indicator; warm-up request on login |
| LockService timeout (10s) → 423 response | Medium | Retry logic in Flutter (max 3 retries with backoff) |
| Apps Script 6-min execution timeout | Low | Keep handlers thin; never process large datasets in one call |
| Google Sheets row limit (~50k practical) | Low | Archive old transactions yearly; acceptable for target business size |
| No real-time sync | Medium | Pull-to-refresh pattern; cache invalidation on mutations |
| KTP OCR accuracy varies by image quality | High | Always show editable confirmation screen; never auto-save OCR result |
| Calendar event out-of-sync on edit failure | Medium | Store calendar_event_id; retry calendar update independently |

### Business / UX Risks
| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Double booking between simultaneous requests | LockService + overlap check before insert |
| Staff accidentally deleting bookings | Confirmation dialog; soft-delete option |
| Lost Apps Script URL | Store in Settings screen; document in onboarding |
| Offline usage | Not supported — show clear "No internet" error state |

